cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.HC

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with analyzing student interactions with online tools, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper discusses how the findings can help instructors to provide procedural guidance and make timely interventions, which relates to the social impact of technology.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses machine learning techniques to analyze the sequences of student transitions between online platforms.
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possible category as the paper deals with analyzing data from blended courses, which involves computational techniques.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also a possible category as the paper discusses how the findings can help instructors to identify harmful habits and provide guidance to the students, which relates to the interaction between humans and computers.
